	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />i think you mean cpu cycle ?    a cpu instruction is at least 2 cpu cycles 
<br />
<br />the emu would be more accurate that way.  however that would probably cause alot of cache misses and extra funciton calls.  this is how nintendulator works (quietust can comment more on his emu).  
<br />
<br />mine does the catch up method, in the cpu i count the cpu cycles and catch up the ppu to the cycle read.   this works for now.  i will try to improve it later.
<br />
<br />matt

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


